# ─── MongoDB ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@<cluster>.mongodb.net/amethystapi?appName=AmethystAPI
# Engine Mongo pool: default maxPoolSize=10 per process (minPoolSize=0, maxIdleTimeMS=30s) unless overridden.
# Driver default without a cap is 100 — on shared Atlas tiers set MONGODB_MAX_POOL_SIZE explicitly if needed.
# MONGODB_MAX_POOL_SIZE=25
# One-off scripts default to maxPoolSize=5 (see src/lib/mongoPoolConfig.ts); override for heavy batch tools:
# MONGODB_SCRIPT_MAX_POOL_SIZE=10
# Optional: override driver appName for Atlas “Client” attribution (default: AmethystEngine).
# MONGODB_APP_NAME=AmethystEngine

# ─── Catalog / valuation hot path ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Licensed HTTP routes (POST /valuation/*, POST /analysis/scarcity, POST /simulation/mock-pick) skip
# MLB Stats API team hydration by default so Draftroom does not wait on statsapi.mlb.com during
# valuation. Sync (`pnpm sync-players`) should persist real team abbreviations.
# Set to 1 only to debug thin AL/NL pools when Mongo still has placeholder teams:
# AMETHYST_ALLOW_HTTP_MLB_TEAM_HYDRATE=1
# Force-skip hydration everywhere (CI, scripts, HTTP): AMETHYST_SKIP_MLB_TEAM_HYDRATE=1
# Extra per-request timing breakdown (logs a second structured line): VALUATION_REQUEST_TIMING=1
#
# In-process catalog cache for the valuation hot path:
#  - loadMongoCatalogForEngine() caches its post-normalize, post-eligibility-filter
#    rows so /valuation/* requests on the same instance skip the full
#    Player.find({}) + normalization (~1.3k rows after roster-universe). Cache is
#    per-process; the API process auto-warms on Mongo connect (so the first request
#    never pays the cold full-collection find), and `pnpm sync-players` drops the
#    cache after its writes (when run in-process) so quality gates see fresh data.
#  - Default TTL: 300000 ms (5 minutes). The catalog only changes when an operator
#    runs `pnpm sync-players`, so a long TTL is safe and dramatically reduces
#    cold-miss latency (no ~7s find on instance startup / pod recycle).
#  - Override TTL (ms, clamp 1..600000):
# AMETHYST_CATALOG_CACHE_TTL_MS=300000
#  - Disable entirely (preferred env name; AMETHYST_CATALOG_CACHE_DISABLED still
#    accepted as a legacy alias):
# AMETHYST_DISABLE_CATALOG_CACHE=1

# ─── Redis ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local dev: redis://localhost:6379
# Production (Upstash — recommended for App Runner, no VPC required):
#   rediss://<user>:<token>@<host>.upstash.io:6380
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
# Cache helpers are non-blocking: getCached/setCache/deleteCache fast-skip when
# the client is not "ready" and race every call against this hard timeout.
# Default 50 ms; clamp 5..500. When Redis is unreachable a licensed request adds
# at most one timeout per cache miss, never seconds of ioredis retry backoff.
# REDIS_CACHE_TIMEOUT_MS=50

# ─── API key validation (defense-in-depth in front of Mongo + Redis) ──────────
# Licensed routes (POST /valuation/*, /catalog/batch-values, /analysis/scarcity,
# /simulation/*, /signals/*) validate `x-api-key` via three layers, in order:
#   1) In-process memo cache (this knob) — sub-ms.
#   2) Redis (when reachable) — coherent across instances; non-blocking.
#   3) Mongo ApiKey.findOne({ keyHash }) — authoritative.
# A populated memo entry skips both Redis and Mongo, so a Redis or Atlas outage
# can no longer add seconds per request for hot keys.
# Default TTL 60000 ms; clamp 1000..600000.
# AMETHYST_API_KEY_MEMO_TTL_MS=60000
# Disable the memo cache entirely (Redis + Mongo only):
# AMETHYST_DISABLE_API_KEY_MEMO_CACHE=1

# ─── Server ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local dev: 3002 (portal + API — same Express app). App Runner production: 8080
PORT=3002
# Browser Origin allowlist (comma-separated). Omit or leave empty to allow any Origin (reflect) — typical for App Runner when portal + API share one URL.
# Restrict in production if needed: CORS_ORIGIN=https://app.example.com,https://www.example.com
# CORS_ORIGIN=

# When the portal HTML is hosted on a different origin than the API, set the API base (https only in prod). Server injects <meta name="amethyst-api-base"> into index.html.
# PORTAL_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com

# ─── Licensing / The Brain ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# API keys live in MongoDB (apikeys). The developer portal can mint one-off keys when enabled:
# Issuance defaults to on if omitted. Use 0 / false / off to disable portal minting.
KEY_ISSUANCE_ENABLED=1
# Optional: require matching header X-Key-Issuance-Token on POST /api/keys/issue (same value).
# KEY_ISSUANCE_SECRET=your-long-random-token

# ─── Draft BFF — news signals webhook (optional global fallback) ────────────────
# Multi-tenant: each API key registers its hook via PATCH /api/account/keys/:id/news-signals-webhook (portal).
# Single URL fallback: Engine also POSTs here if set (same payload + Bearer rules).
# Bearer: INTERNAL_WEBHOOK_SECRET if set, else AMETHYST_API_KEY (same plaintext Draft uses as x-api-key).
# DRAFT_NEWS_SIGNALS_WEBHOOK_URL=https://draft.example.com/api/internal/news-signals/hook
# INTERNAL_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# AMETHYST_API_KEY=
#
# Webhook payload (Draftroom-facing):
#   { event: "signals_updated", source: "engine",
#     fingerprint: "<sha256-of-stable-signals-body>",
#     count: <int>, occurred_at: "<ISO>" }
# `fingerprint` is computed from `{count, signals}` only (NOT `fetched_at`),
# so a no-op MLB poll produces an identical fingerprint and is suppressed
# at the Engine before any POST. Draftroom can additionally body-dedupe on
# (event, source, fingerprint) to defend against any cross-instance fan-out.
#
# Per-URL in-process dedupe + throttle (defense in depth — works when Redis
# is unreachable, which is the production default since App Runner has no
# REDIS_URL set today):
#  - Same `fingerprint` → never POSTed twice to the same URL.
#  - Default min interval between same-fingerprint sends: 5000 ms
#    (override; clamp 0..60000):
# AMETHYST_NEWS_WEBHOOK_MIN_INTERVAL_MS=5000
#  - Disable in-process dedupe entirely (debug only — every cache miss
#    will fan out):
# AMETHYST_DISABLE_NEWS_WEBHOOK_DEDUPE=1
